
Williamsburg, 5 Apr. 1780. Encloses Maj. Quarles return of men raised in his last tour; Quarles complains extremely of inattention of[345] county lieutenants to the execution of laws which fall within their departments. He has also applied for compensation for his services; six hundred dollars per month is recommended. Signed by Innes and Barron. Countersigned: April 5. 1780. I approve of the allowance of six hundred dollars per month. Th: Jefferson.
